Yemen: Cholera Response Weekly Epidemiological Bulletin: W43 2017 (23-29 Oct)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The cumulative total from 27 Apr 2017 to 29 Oct 2017 is 890 017 suspected cholera cases and 2185 associated deaths, (CFR 0.25 percent). A total of 960 have been confirmed by culture. The total proportion of severe cases among the suspected cases is 19 percent. The national attack rate is 323.1 per 10 000. Children under 5 years old represent 27.1 percent of total suspected cases.

The 5 governorates with the highest cumulative attack rates per 10 000 remain Amran (750), Al Mahwit (706), Al Dhale'e (633), Abyan (487) and Sana'a (440).

In total, 17 896 rapid diagnostic tests (RDT) have been performed which represents 20.1 percent coverage. A total of 2219 cultures have been performed which represents 22.3percent coverage. The last positive culture was on [21 Oct 2017] in Dar Sad district (Aden governorate)

Among the 305 affected districts, 39 districts did not report any suspected case the last 3 consecutive weeks.

Governorate and District level:
The trend at country level over the past 3 weeks is considered decreased. At governorate level, the trend from W40-W42 decrease or was stable in all governorates. No governorate is reporting a CFR higher than 1 percent.

Trends:
The weekly number of cases is decreasing for the 7th consecutive week.
The weekly proportion of children under 5 is as twice as week 26 (18 percent in week 26 and 39 percent in week 43).
The weekly proportion of severe cases has significantly decreased representing now 9 percent of the admitted cases.
The use of RDTs has significantly increased since week 40.

Week 43:
26 137 suspected cases and 5 associated deaths were reported.
9 percent are severe cases -1252 RDTs were performed, 301 were positive

--
